SIMPLE: fourfold
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fourfold
<hw>Four"fold`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a. & adv.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>fe⟦oacute⟧werfeold</ets>.]</ety> <def>Four times; quadruple;
<as>as, a <ex>fourfold</ex> division</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He shall restore the lamb <qex>fourfold</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>2 Sam.
xii. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fourfold</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fourfold
<hw>Four"fold`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Four times as many or as
much.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fourfold</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Fourfold
<hw>Four"fold`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make four times as much or
as many, as an assessment; to quadruple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fourfooted</ent>⟦br⟧
